================================================================================
LICENSE COMPATIBILITY NOTES
================================================================================

1. MIT License (Nubicustos)
   - Highly permissive, compatible with almost all open-source licenses
   - Allows commercial use, modification, and distribution

2. GPL-Licensed Tools (ScoutSuite GPL-2.0, CloudSploit GPL-3.0, Neo4j GPL-3.0)
   - These tools are used via Docker orchestration, not embedded or modified
   - Docker container isolation maintains license separation
   - Users who modify these tools directly must comply with GPL requirements

3. AGPL-Licensed Tools (Grafana AGPL-3.0)
   - Used as a standalone visualization service
   - Network use does not trigger AGPL distribution requirements for Nubicustos
   - Users modifying Grafana itself must comply with AGPL

4. Apache 2.0 Licensed Tools (majority)
   - Fully compatible with MIT License
   - Patent grant included
   - Requires preservation of copyright notices

================================================================================

For complete license texts, please refer to the LICENSE files in each tool's
respective repository or Docker image.

If you have questions about licensing or attribution, please open an issue on
the Nubicustos GitHub repository.
